{"lemma":"مُتَشابِهِي","slug":"مُتَشابِهِي","root":"ش.ب.ه","root_slug":"ش-ب-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ب-ه","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُتَشابِه","root":"شبه","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21653"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%87%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of تَشَابَهَ (tašābaha)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"similar, resembling"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ambiguous"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of تَشَابَهَ (tašābaha, “to look like”)."},"ipa":["/mu.ta.ʃaː.bih/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21653","headword_ar":"مُتَشَابِهٌ","root":"$bh","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Consimilar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conformable, in its several parts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta$aAbihFA","text_ar":"مُتَشَابِهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means in the Kur xxxix. 24. (Jel.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta$aAbihaAtN","text_ar":"مُتَشَابِهَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"Things"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling, one another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$otabihN","text_ar":"مُشْتَبِهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta$aAbihaAtN","text_ar":"مُتَشَابِهَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur iii. 5 means Verses that are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equivocal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ambiguous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"susceptible of different interpretations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh:) or verses"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unintelligible;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the commencements [of many] of the chapters: (Jel:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta$aAbih","text_ar":"مُتَشَابِه"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur is that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the meaning is not to be learned from its words;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is of two sorts; one is that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the meaning is known by referring it to what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHokam","text_ar":"مُحْكَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; and the other is that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the knowledge of its real meaning is not attainable in any way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it means what is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not understood without repeated con-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1501},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sideration:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fsr","text_ar":"فسر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) Ed-Dahhák is related to have explained"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHokamaAtu","text_ar":"المُحْكَمَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ what have not been abrogated; ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuta$aAbihaAtu","text_ar":"المُتَشَابِهَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what have been abrogated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.)"}],"source_refs":["Ksh","Jel","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}